
<!-- Chosen Palette: Calm Neutrals with Blue/Green/Amber accents -->
<!-- Application Structure Plan: The application now starts with a login screen. Upon entry, the primary view is a "Collaboration Hub" for data scanning and team chat. Scan history is now saved per-user. The file upload option has been removed to streamline the interface. The detailed strategic guides have been replaced with a concise "Prevention Strategies" section at the bottom. The admin panel is enhanced to show user IDs and passwords for monitoring purposes. -->
<!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
- Report Info: The core 3-pillar structure (Policy, Technology, People). Goal: Organize/Inform. Viz/Presentation: A new, concise card-based layout for prevention tips, derived from the original pillar structure. Interaction: Simple, readable cards without complex interactions. Justification: Provides direct, easy-to-digest advice as requested by the user, replacing the previous multi-section layout.
- Report Info: (New) User-provided data for scanning and team chat. Goal: Organize/Inform/Engage. Viz/Presentation: A simplified layout with a data input area, a results panel, and a simulated chat interface. Interaction: Users can paste text, click "scan" to see simulated leak detection results (now including link checks) saved to their private history, and add messages to a shared chat log. Justification: Simplifies the user experience.
- Report Info: (New) Scan result analysis. Goal: Compare. Viz/Presentation: A dynamic doughnut chart showing the percentage of leaks by risk level. The file-specific chart has been removed. Interaction: Chart updates automatically after a scan. Justification: Provides an immediate, easy-to-digest visual summary of scan findings.
- Report Info: (New) Admin session monitoring. Goal: Inform. Viz/Presentation: An enhanced admin panel with a table of logged-in users showing their simulated ID and password, a view of the shared chat, and a new accordion view for every user's scan history. Interaction: This panel is only visible to the admin. Justification: Fulfills the requirement for an admin-specific view to monitor all simulated activity.
- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
<!DOCTYPE html>
